translated: Högbom, Emmy Augusta was a teacher at a high school in Halmstad. She was born on May 23rd, 1894 in Tröii-ninge, Halland County, Sweden. Her parents were Sven Nyman and Anna Johansson. She married Sigurd Högbom, who was also a high school teacher, in 1928. She received her bachelor's degree in Lund in 1914, her bachelor's degree in philosophy in 1917, and her master's degree in philosophy in 1919. She traveled to Berlin, Paris, and London in 1921, England and Scotland in 1924 and 1935, Germany, Austria, and Hungary in 1926, Belgium and France in 1931, Norway in 1919, 1933, 1938, and 1947, the Soviet Union in 1936, and Finland in 1939. She was a substitute teacher at Lunds fullst. lärov. f. fil. from 1919, in Hälsingborg from 1920 to 1921, and in Åmål from 1921 to 1924 and from 1925 to 1927. She was a substitute subject teacher in Gävle in 1928, a subject teacher there from 1929 to 1937, and a teacher of German and English at Halmstad High School since 1937. She was also the Chairperson of the Lund Women's Student Association in 1918.
